Public Sub GoNewboy()
'Create a new folder
'This is made difficult by the fact that there is no inbuilt way
'to refresh the treeview. You need to clear a block of memory
'and then re-allocate.... too hard, sorry. We know exactly where the window is
'and exactly what its doing, so lets just press OK, then
'relaunch it in precisely the same condition, except now
'it will be updated with our new folder in place and opened
'at that folder. Slight flash on screen, but thats all.
Dim temp As String, tmpDir As String
tmpDir = StripTerminator(CurrentDir)
starthere:
If Right(tmpDir, 1) = "\" Then tmpDir = Left(tmpDir, Len(tmpDir) - 1)
temp = InputBox("Enter a name for your new folder" + vbCrLf + tmpDir + "\...", BB.TitleBar)
If Len(Trim(temp)) = 0 Then Exit Sub
If FileExists(tmpDir + "\" + temp) Then
    MsgBox "A Folder of that name already exists." + vbCrLf + "Enter a different name and try again.", vbCritical, BB.TitleBar
    GoTo starthere
End If
MkDir tmpDir + "\" + temp
BB.InitDir = tmpDir + "\" + temp 'set the new start folder
Newboy = True
'Clean up and close the window so we can re-open at the new folder
Call pUnSubClass
Call pUnSubClassDlg
Call pUnSubClassEdit
Call pUnSubClassFS
Call SendMessage(CancelbuttonWindow, BM_CLICK, 0, 0)
